_meanings:
{@--1@} To know, understand, 
comprehend; {#kramAdamuM nArada ityaboDi saH#}  
<ls>Śi. 1. 3</ls>; <ls n="Śi.">9. 24</ls>; {#nAbudDa kalpadrumatAM vihAya#}
{#jAtaM tamAtmanyasipatravfkzaM#} <ls>R. 14. 48</ls>;
{#yadi buDyate hariSiSuH stanaMDayaH#}  
<ls>Bv. 1. 53.</ls>

{@--2@} To perceive, notice, recognise,
mark; {#hiraRmayaM rhaMsamaboDi nEzaDaH#}  
<ls>N. 1. 117</ls>; {#api laMDitamaDvAnaM bubuDe na#} 
{#buDopamaH#} <ls>R. 1. 47</ls>; <ls n="R.">12. 39.</ls>

{@--6@} To wake up, awake, rise from
sleep; {#dadadapi giramaMtarbuDyate no manuzyaH#}
<ls>Śi. 11. 4</ls>; {#te ca prApurudanvaMtaM bubuDe#} 
{#cAdipUruzaH#} <ls>R. 10. 6.</ls>

{@--7@} To regain 
consciousness, to come to one's senses;
{#SanEraboDi sugrIvaH so'luMcItkarRanAsikaM#}
<ls>Bk. 15. 57.</ls>

{@--5@} To
remind, put in mind of; {#smarziyati#}
{#tvAM na sa boDito'pi san#} <ls>Ś. 4. 1.</ls>

{@--6@} To
wake up, rouse, excite (<ab>fig.</ab>); {#akAle#}
{#boDito BrAtrA#} <ls>R. 12. 81</ls>, <ls n="R.">5. 75.</ls>

{@--8@} To cause to expand, open;  
{#maDuravA maDuboDitamADavI#} <ls>Śi. 6. 20</ls>; {#savitA#}
{#boDayati paMkajAnyeva#} <ls>Ś. 5. 28.</ls>
